task.summary: Default task

healing - added IHealFormula and DefaultHealFormula - added IApplyHealScript and 2 variants - changed DefaultApplyDamageScript to ApplyAttackDamageScript - added ApplyNonAttackDamageScript variant - added HealComponent - added skill and spell HealScript - added OnHealed to all creature scripts - consumables now use non-alerting damage or heal functional scripts to apply their effect

BulkEditTool, bugfixes - created BulkEditTool, a code-interactive way to manipulate all of the json files via code - fixed a bug causing you to lose current weight when swapping an item with an empty slot - fixed a bug causing timed events to not properly serialize and deserialize - added more logging around reloading - added more logging around command execution - added manaBasedDamageComponent

ChannelService, IP Lockout - if a player attempts to log in or change the password too many times in a limited period of time, they will be temporarily locked out (configurable) - moved CommandInterceptor to Chaos.Messaging namespace - added ChannelService, which handled channel-based messaging - you can now configure default channels that will be created on server startup, and added as default channels to new characters (they can opt to leave them after logging in) - added a number of commands around managing chat channels - moved all admin commands to their own folder - group chat is now available via the channel service - fixed a bug causing you to not be able to pick up items in a stack if the top item was too heavy - added truncation to public and server messages
documentation - fixed a bug causing monsters to not aggro

Dialog rework, Circles, Stock - added several interfaces that build on IDialogSourceEntity to give extra details depending on the kind of dialog - added "Contextual" to dialogs, to allow users to specify when state needs to be passed - added "Context" to dialogs, which gets passed based on the "Contextual" flag - removed InputCollector - reworked all built in dialogs to not use InputCollector and instead use Contextual - Dialog.Text is no longer editable beyond injecting arguments - added "Top" keyword, see documentation - reworked how the previous button works, so that it works well with contextual dialogs - added more logging around public and private messages (logged as trace) - added a RequiresMaster check to the built in EquipmentScript - added reactor checks to AmbushScript - added easy ways to check for blocking/nonblocking reactors - added IStockService to track the stock of items in shops - moved metadata into it's own project and touched it up - ComplexActionHelper.BuyItem takes an optional Shop argument and handles stock checks - MenuOrDialogType is now ChaosDialogType - added DeepClone utility, still kinda testing it tho - rewrote Inject extension to be far more performant - added ability to set the "Origin" of an IIntervalTimer, emulating that the interval timer was starting at that origin time - added ICircle / Circle and a bunch of extensions for ICircle - added lots of documentation across many classes - added Dialogs article - fixed a bug where if an ability moves a player, activation context does not take into account their most recent position
ignore api folder
ignore api folder
docfx update
docs generation runs on windows (cuz i have wpf projects in the solution)
fix package issues
fix another package issue
Documentation - and some small fixes

Documentation, bugfixes - fixed several bugs in the LearnSpellScript (beware copypasting) - fixed usage of inventory for stacked items - fixed WithdrawGold dialog script - fixed ApplyNonAlertingHealScript, which would prevent any healing above 0, instead of healing below 0 - fixed a bug in dialogs where using .Reply() in OnNext would not stop the dialog from progressing - added documentation to Chaos.Networking
initial setup instructions
fix docs api homepage
added a default timed snore for afk - multiple other minor fixes

Item throttling, documentation - Items are now correctly throttled by MaxActionsPerSecond / ActionThrottle - added MaxItemsPerSecond to WorldOptions - Items are additionally throttled by MaxItemsPerSecond / ItemThrottle - moved some more configuration stuff into configurers - added a documentation article for Items
minor fixes - fix for 1+ line spells - fix Poison and Regeneration script name

minor fixes, documentation - fixed a bug causing shutdowns to not properly save aislings - simplified shutdown command, the message the command takes is just an initial message now - moved ApproachTime to Creature, all creatures record approaches automatically - added monster.ResetAggro() and an overload for specific ids - added an /invite commands that works across maps - added /adminkick and /adminban commands - added an article in the documentation about commands

Visibility system, IdGenerator rework - added a Visibility system, read the article to understand it - rewrote ClientId and ServerId into 3 classes, EphemeralRandomIdGenerator.cs, SequentialIdGenerator.cs, and PersistentIdGenerator.cs - redirects now use the EphemeralRandomIdGenerator - combined options configuration and validation into a couple of classes - item and creature sprites are no longer offset during object creation, and are instead offset purely in the networking layer during serialization - RedirectManager now throws away redirects that are more than 10s old - various other minor cleanups

Minor refactor, Visibility touch ups - moved a number of namespaces around - Containers > Collections - Commands > Messaging - Clients > Networking - Objects > Models - Data > Models.Data (and others) - Configuration > Services.Configuration - finished the visibility system - created VisibilityComponent and added it to DefaultAislingScript and DefaultScript (Monster) - added hide/see hide spells - added hide/see hide effects
Fake skill level - abilities now display in the panel with a fake level 100/100, to allow for learnable abilities to show up in metadata - re-added file based logging

Component system rework - reworked components - wrote a bunch more components - wrote an article about components - rewrote most of the item/skill/spell/reactor scripts to use the new component system
components article corrections

Improved update loop - created UpdatableCollection, a collection that will allow me to avoid copying the collection, and iterating it a 2nd time - changed StressTest command to Stress command - changed monster scripts to update if an aisling is on the map, rather than if an aisling is in their view - fixed typos in documentation

minor things - add some functionality around collision - hidden admins have no collision - setting you class re-sends the UserId packet so that metadata will update - Exchange useroption will now be honored - re-added optional wall collision to cascading abilities - re-added functionality to GenerateCardinalPoints even though it is duplicative - decoupled Chaos.Pathfinding implementations

minor changes - fixed sleep animation occurring when logging in - "metafile" is now "metadata" - chanttimer now uses timespans instead of milliseconds (there was a loss of precision) - added several mappers for objects that were just using direct conversions - if Mapper fails to find a mapper using the types provided, it will search the interface and basetype hierarchy for a mapper
more minor changes

Server Synchronization / DynamicVars Optimization - all lobby/login packet handlers, and any world packetHandler that does not use map synchronization will now use server synchronization - dynamicVars now caches the result the first time a script var is deserialized - other minor fixes

Partial guilds, Logging makeover - added GuildStore, GuildFactory, Guild, and related schema types and mapper - added GuildManagementScript and GuildCreateScript - guilds are saved and backed up at regular configurable intervals - guilds also use channels, and thus have some configuration in appsettings.json just like groups - reworked some existing classes to consolidate storage interfaces/basetypes (AislingStore) - wrote LogEvent class to help log extra properties to underlying loggers - removed NLog.Targets.Seq and replaced with a target of my own creation - moved logging configuration into it's own json file - logfile target now logs using structured logging - created the .WithProperty / .WithProperties ILogger extensions that will allow you to add extra objects as context to the log message - used these new methods throughout the project with the idea of keeping the rendered message concise (no complex objects), and if you want more detail you can explore the structured logs in the file or in seq - did a full pass on logs to clean them up and make sure i was logging what i wanted to, when i wanted to - minor changes to the registered object transformers in startup - added Guild object transformer - minor changes to IRectangle.GetRandomPoint() to allow for a predicate - added an extension method to help with intercardinal directions (Extensions.Geometry) - moved Serialization/Deserialization + Mapping into a new class EntityRepository, the overwhelming majority of serialization/deserialization should now be through this class
use docfx 2.67.1
missed a small documentation update

Documentation, Logging, Guilds - finished up the rest of the guild related sample scripts - removed .WithProperties due to issues with sometimes having a string as the 3rd or 4th property causing the wrong method to be called - all .WithProperties converted to .WithProperty chained calls - added documentation for Skills.md and Spells.md - added a couple mapper profiles for some more small things - added configurable world options for LootDropsLockToRewardTargetSecs and GroundItemDespawnTimeMins

Bugfixes, Tests - validated behaviors of Abstractions and Extensions projects - fixed a number of bugs in those projects - wrote tests for those projects - consolidated nuget package versions that previously escaped somehow - resolved code inspection issues

More tests & bugfixes - GuildStoreOptions now properly checks for a backupPath that is a subpath of directory - CounterCollection.TryDecrement now properly returns false if it would have decremented a value to below 0 - DynamicVars.GetRequired<T> now no longer throws a NullReferenceException if it found a key but that key has a default value - removed ReferenceEqualityComparer, an identical class already exists in the .net runtime - RandomExtensions.Next<T>() now correctly returns a decimal between 0 and 1 - TypeExtensions.IsPrimitive() now correctly returns true for decimal (decimal is somenow not a true primitive type in the runtime) - removed RollSingle and RollDouble from DecimalRandomizer, dice rolls dont make sense for decimals - IntegerRandomizer.PickRandomWeightedSingleOrDefault<T>() now correctly calculates the "chanceOfSelection"
Item modification changes - pivoting to support a system where items are modified by adding additional scripts, rather than manually changing modifiers and having them serialize
BulkEditTool upgrades - BulkEditTool can now create, delete, modify, and view items - added an extension for scripted objects that allows you to add a script at runtime
Error handling for BulkEditTool - when a Repository fails to serialize or deserialize an object, the exception should be wrapped and rethrown to include the path of the failing json
Minor things - fixed MonsterSpawns not obeying SpawnArea - added CTRL+F functionality to BulkEditTool for both the Grid View and List View
more minor fixes

BulkEditTool optimization - ItemEditor controls are no longer created on initializing, they are instead created when an item in the ListView is first selected (this speeds up startup time by a huge amount)
ChaosTool - renamed BulkEditTool to ChaosTool - added some documentation for ChaosTool - added the ability to modify dialogs, skills, and spells to ChaosTool - added the ability to modify ScriptKeys
ChaosTool bugfixes - fixed a bug where ListViews of strings were not persisting updates correctly
MonsterSpawn, Tests - migrated 4 properties from MonsterSpawn (monsters.json) to MonsterTemplate - more unit tests - fixed binding of pure strings in ListViews

FuzzySearch / Verbal Banking - added string extensions for calculating sorensen-dice coefficient and levenshtein distance - added several more string extensions that use those to perform fuzzy searches (FuzzySearch, FuzzySearchBy, FuzzyContains) - added verbal banking scripts that utilize fuzzy searches to be lenient of mispellings, punctuation, and plurality - trimmed away some unnecessary extensions projects - unit tests for fuzzy searches and dependent extensions - removed the built in ability of panel methods that take in strings to also look up template keys - added a new set of methods to Panel and Inventory that explicitly take and operate on template keys instead of template name / displayname - TryGiveItem now takes a ref Item, because if that item is stackable, there's a good chance it will be merged into an existing stack. The merged item will replace the ref item passed in - changed ItemScript.OnPickup and ReactorTileScript.OnItemPickedUpFrom to take in the originalItem and originalCount, to make it clear that it may not be the current item - cleaned up some old pieces of documentation

misc - merged many events from merchant, monster, and aisling scripts to be generic across all creatures - finished guild dialogs - guild/rank touch ups - added HelpText for commands - added help/commands command - creatures now have trackers instead of just aislings - added a number of tracked things to trackers - fixed some bugs with dialogs in ChaosTool - added logging to verbal banking - merchants now have a WanderIntervalMs and BlackList - created an extremely simple WanderScript for merchants - wander now correctly obeys blacklist

Verbal Shop - added VerbalShop scripts that allow for buying and selling items verbally - added Restock command - ISellShopSource.ItemsToBuy will now be faux items rather than just template keys - a command can now have multiple CommandAttributes

Refactor / DirectoryBackupService - split BackedUpStore away from IStore / IAsyncStore into DirectoryBackupService - refactored project with some updates file layout rules - fixed broken links in documentation - wrote tests for Chaos.Messaging - added a batch file under Tests/Reports that will generate an opencover code coverage report and generate a webpage from the report
Re-add merchant pathing bounds
